Could a Historian help me understand this...</span><hr size=1> Recently a friend of mine who just started to play eq, asked me what I think I have been thinking for such a long time but never thought to ask...<br>
<br>
What are the significancy of the Mugs/Steins in EQ?  His point is he can understand the voodoo doll look for casters, but why would a caster use a Mug/Stein.<br>
<br>
You know for the life of me I couldnt answer this question... I guess I just took it in stride and thought to myself well at least its not a moss covered twig....<br>
<br>
In either case is there a story behind the Steins of Mag and other Steins, a larger quest that I dont know about?<br>
