Maidens of Faydark</a></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bbrellserilis.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=wabadoodles>Wabadoodles</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#CC9900>(9/6/01 8:51:07 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.brellserilis.net/images/posticons/bardtr.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Could a Historian help me understand this...</span><hr size=1> As far as I know, the mugs and things are for casters and such..they add wisdon, dexterity, intelligince (SP), things like that. If you're talkin' about something else, like something BIGGER and BETTER, I dunno..never seen one, I don't think. But the mugs that you see Wizards and Chanters, and other caster classes using add stats (listed above). <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  'Tis all I know, M'lady..Farewell and Goodbye<br>
<br>
   -Wabin Peaceweaver <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uxandrith.showPublicProfile?language=EN>xandrith</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#CC9900>(9/7/01 8:58:15 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.brellserilis.net/images/posticons/bardtr.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Could a Historian help me understand this...</span><hr size=1> Maybe its not the mug at all. Maybe its something that is part of the mug. Think of an amulet - it isn't the necklace itself that is magical it is the stone mounted inside it. Could be the same with the mugs. May not be the mugs themselvs but maybe some inlayed gems that have magical properties that give the wizard the enhanced stats. Why a mug you ask? not sure only thing i can think of is this - a Guard would be less likley to stop you if all he saw was a mug instead of a weapon. Plus, at least in renaissance times, mugs were carried on the person hanging from the belt. So it wouldnt be odd to see someone carrying a mug around. <br>
<br>
Anywho thats my 2 cents. hope it helps<br>
<br>
Jorgan Swiftnote lvl 43 bard Sphere of Honor <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueannyarah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eannyarah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#CC9900>(9/10/01 1:59:59 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.brellserilis.net/images/posticons/beertr.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Could a Historian help me understand this...</span><hr size=1> My guess is that casters like ale just as much as anyone else...  I know I do...  Actually, I've been thinking about this one for the last week.  Yes, the mugs and steins add stats to the characters, but that's not the question.  To try to answer the question, my input would be put thusly (sorry, I've just always wanted to say that...): In the Rennaissance period, you would quite often see people with steins and mugs tied to their belts and being carried in their hands.  This was because your average household would have enough flatware/silverware/whatnot for just their immediate family.  To avoid trying to drink mead from their hands, travelers would simply carry the simple luxuries, i.e. mugs, etc., with them to avoid putting their generous hosts on the spot when they had no cups to drink from.<br>
<br>
Hope that helps! <p>"How can I kill you if you keep stunning me?" ~Eannyarah </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufenye.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fenye</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Queen of Discord</span><br>  Posts: 2268<br> <font color=#CC9900>(9/11/01 3:28:23 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://people.mn.mediaone.net/timelord81/images/fenye.jpg hieght=285 width=129 ></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.brellserilis.net/images/posticons/beertr.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Could a Historian help me understand this...</span><hr size=1> Actually my theory is that some goofball employee of verant made a cup on the graphics design program, showed it to his friends, and then it was put in the game as a joke.<br>
<br>
But.. seriously, take the Stein. The crude stein, the lesser one, adds charisma. When you are drunk, you are, for the most part, much more charismatic. at least for a little while. The charismatic properties of alcohol was probably magically added into the stien.<br>
<br>
The stein of mogguk. Maybe Mogguk was a powerful caster who wanted to create a magical item to counter the intelligence penalties that come when you drink ale. If he liked to drink alot of ale, but didn't want to suffer the INT penalties (as much), then it made sense to him to make an item that he could not only drink his ale from, but also magically create an intelligence buffer for him so he wasn't so stupid when he drank.<br>
<br>
<br>
oh well, my best shot. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisroleplaying.showMessage?topicID=424.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisroleplaying.showMessage?topicID=421.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisroleplaying.threadControl?topicID=350.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisroleplaying.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=350.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisroleplaying.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=350.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="brellserilisfrm67">Today's News<option value="brellserilisfrm48">Town Crier (Rules & Announcements)<option value="brellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion">The Commons (General EQ Discussion)<option value="brellserilisroleplaying">The Tavern (Roleplaying)<option value="brellserilisfrm66">Rants Link<option value="brellserilisfrm56">Salutations & Congratulations <option value="brellserilisfrm33">Dreams & Diversions (Off Topic)<option value="brellserilisfrm55">Fellowship of Guilds (Guildchat)<option value="brellserilisfrm64">Archived Threads<option value="brellserilisbrellslairadminonly">Brell's Lair (Admin only)<option value="brellserilismeleetalk">Tome: